<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-515-244  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 515 244.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  August 1 1989* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Malaysia: police fight computer fraud.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Worsley, Michael; Roowi, S.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer crimesMalaysiaFraudCredit.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>MALAYSIA: POLICE FIGHT COMPUTER FRAUD KUALA LUMPUR, MALAYSIA, 1989 JUL 22(NB) -- The police here plans to form a unit specially for handlingcomputer-related crimes and credit card fraud.andP;  At present, a deputysuperintendent and an inspector who have some knowledge of computertechnology are handling computer fraud cases.andP;  The unit, to be staffed bycomputer experts, will be under the control of the Commercial Crime Branch atpolice headquarters here, according to Deputy CID Director Datuk ShamsuriHaji Arshad.andP;  &quot;We are sensitive to incidents of computer-related crimes bothhere and overseas and are closely following the development of such crimeshere,&quot; he said.andP;  The Malaysian police are expected to seek the assistance oftheir counterparts in Hong Kong, Britain, the US and other countries insetting up the unit.andP;  (Michael Worsley andamp; S.Roowi/19890725)</TEXT></DOC>